#Description
Create a hostPath PersistentVolume named busybox-pv with storage 10Gi, access modes ReadWriteOnce, storageClassName manual, and volume at /mnt/data.
Then create a persistent volume claim, named as busybox-pvc of 3Gi  storage and ReadWriteOnce access mode and make sure it should be bound status.
Once done, update the pod created in question2 to mount the busybox-pvc at /tmp/test location.

#Manifest.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: busybox-pv
  labels:
    type: local
spec:
  storageClassName: manual
  capacity:
    storage: 10Gi
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  hostPath:
    path: "/mnt/data"

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: busybox-pvc
spec:
  storageClassName: manual
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 3Gi

---
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  creationTimestamp: null
  labels:
    run: busybox
  name: busybox
spec:
  nodeSelector:
    app: busybox
  containers:
  - image: busybox
    name: busybox
    command: ["/bin/bash", "sh", "sleep 3600"]
    volumeMounts:
    - mountPath: "/tmp/test"
      name: busybox-pvc
    resources: {}
  dnsPolicy: ClusterFirst
  restartPolicy: Never
  volumes:
  - name: busybox-pvc
    persistentVolumeClaim:
      claimName: busybox-pvc 
status: {} 
#